{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 \u9881 ?\u65039 ? 1. Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ReaImGui must be installed to use JKK_Visualizer.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi0 ReaImGui is an essential library that allows for modern user interfaces within REAPER. Since this script's UI is entirely built on ReaImGui, it is a required component.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Install {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://reapack.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
ReaPack
}}}
} The easiest and safest way to install ReaImGui is through {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://reapack.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
{\b ReaPack}
}}}
. Please refer to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://reapack.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
the ReaPack websit
}}}
 for the installation guide. Once installed, you will see an {\b Extensions \u8594 ? ReaPack} menu in REAPER's top menu bar.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Install ReaImGui}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Navigate to {\b Extensions \u8594 ? ReaPack \u8594 ? Browse Packages}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Search for {\f1 ReaImGui}. (If it doesn't appear, follow the guide at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/cfillion/reaimgui"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
{\b this site}
}}}
)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Right-click the {\b ReaImGui / Extensions} package and select {\b Install}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Click {\b Apply} in the bottom right corner.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Restart REAPER after the installation is complete.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Verify ReaImGui Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Open REAPER\u8217's Action List (Shortcut: {\f1 ?}).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Search for {\f1 ImGui}. If you see a script named {\b ReaImGui: Demo.lua}, the installation was successful.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Import JKK_Visualizer Repository\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Go to Extensions \u8594 ? ReaPack \u8594 ? Manage repositories.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Select Import/export... \u8594 ? Import repositories.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Enter the following URL and click OK:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li1440 \fi0 {\f1 https://github.com/junkikim-sound/JKK_Visualizer/raw/master/index.xml}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Find {\b JKK_Visualizer} in the package list, right-click to {\b install}, and click {\b Apply}. \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab You can now find and run JKK_Visualizer and JKK_Visualizer Editor in your Actions. \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab Add on Master track {\f1 JKK_Visualizer}(jsfx file, you can find this in FX window). and Run the Action {\f1 JKK_Visualizer} \sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 \u55357 ?\u56960 ? 2. Introduction\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\cf1 [image: https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/908ef485-3651-493e-9ec7-62b69f6dda90]\cf0}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Key Features\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Multi-Module Interface}: Monitor LUFS, Goniometer, Symbiote, Scope, and Spectrum modules simultaneously on a single screen.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Dynamic Symbiote}: A unique visualizer that evolves based on low-frequency responses, allowing you to "feel" the sound texture.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Customizable Order}: Use the ImGui-based Editor to reorder modules and adjust sensitivity or theme colors in real-time.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Global Speed Control}: Manage the Attack/Release response speed of all modules via a single master variable. You can adjust response speed by mouse wheel.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Technical Details\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Language: Lua\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Library: REAPER v7.0+ / Dear ImGui\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Engine: JSFX-to-Lua Data Streaming via gmem\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Optimization: Optimized for low CPU usage even at a smooth 60FPS\sa180\par}
